This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an innovative deep reinforcement learning approach for job scheduling in data centers. It also involves the use of an actor-critic model, which is a common technique in deep reinforcement learning. Additionally, it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with scheduling jobs in data centers, which are distributed computing environments. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI, cs.SY (Systems and Control) as job scheduling involves controlling the allocation of resources, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed approach involves the use of neural networks.
